Personally, I have a lot of respect for Dwayne Johnson. I suppose I began to notice him starting with his excellent work in Be Cool where he proved he has plenty of talent. The man came out of costumed choreographed wrestling for crissakes... and is now a top ten box office action star. Action stars kind of have a limit to what they can do with their roles, and like, say, Bruce Willis, Mr. Johnson has pushed his roles to the limits and carried the films he's starred in. I'm gonna say it... I'd like to see a sequel to The Rundown. If any of his critics here are half as successful... I'd give them half as much respect. Hell... if any of his critics have more than 100 bucks in their bank account, I'd slap 'em on the back and tell them to keep up the good work...
